At a mountain ski resort a tandem pilot is looking for clients, spots a pretty girl and asks her whether she would like to make a flight on a paraglider. She is hesitant at first, asks whether it's safe, whether she's supposed to have some special skills. The pilot assures her that it's completely safe and he will instruct her what to do to make a perfect take off. She finally agrees, the pilot straps her in, she is preoccupied with examining her harness and does not take much heed of what's happening behind her. When the pilot's ready he says "Now run", they start to run, make an easy take off and just glide away from the slope. Immediately after taking off, the girl starts muttering to herself "Oh, what a fool I am, why did I do it, what I'm gonna do now, how I'm gonna land" etc. After some time the pilot bends over to her and asks "Are you ok"? The girl, startled, cries out "WHO'S THERE???" via
